{
  "info": {
    "name": "OpenCASE API",
    "description": "Complete Postman collection for the OpenCASE CASE Provider & Management API.\n\n## Setup\n1. Import an environment file (Local / Staging / Production)\n2. Set `tenant_id`, `client_id`, `client_secret` etc. in your active environment\n3. Use the **Get Access Token** request (under Auth) to obtain a Bearer token — it auto-saves to `access_token`\n4. Run **Get CFPackage** to auto-populate all entity IDs (`item_id`, `association_id`, `subject_id`, etc.)\n5. All authenticated endpoints inherit the Bearer token from the collection\n\n## Folders\n- **Auth** — Token requests (client_credentials, password grant)\n- **Public** — Unauthenticated endpoints (health, tenant lookup, discovery)\n- **CASE Provider v1p0** — Standard CASE 1.0 read endpoints\n- **CASE Provider v1p1** — Standard CASE 1.1 read endpoints\n- **Management › Tenants** — Tenant CRUD (requires `case.admin`)\n- **Management › CFPackages** — Framework create/import/delete/restore\n- **Management › CFDocuments** — Document update/delete\n- **Management › CFItems** — Item update/delete\n- **Management › CFAssociations** — Association update/delete\n- **Management › Licenses** — License listing\n- **Management › API Keys** — API key CRUD (requires `case.owner` or `case.admin`)",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "auth": {
    "type": "bearer",
    "bearer": [
      {
        "key": "token",
        "value": "{{access_token}}",
        "type": "string"
      }
    ]
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Auth",
      "description": "Token requests against the Keycloak OIDC endpoint.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Get Token (client_credentials)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.environment.set('access_token', json.access_token);",
                  "  pm.test('Token received', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(json.access_token).to.be.a('string');",
                  "  });",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/x-www-form-urlencoded" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "urlencoded",
              "urlencoded": [
                { "key": "grant_type", "value": "client_credentials" },
                { "key": "client_id", "value": "{{client_id}}" },
                { "key": "client_secret", "value": "{{client_secret}}" }
              ]
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{keycloak_realm_url}}/protocol/openid-connect/token",
              "host": ["{{keycloak_realm_url}}"],
              "path": ["protocol", "openid-connect", "token"]
            },
            "description": "Obtain an access token using the `client_credentials` grant.\n\nSet `client_id` and `client_secret` from an API key. The token is auto-saved to the `access_token` environment variable."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Token (password grant)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.environment.set('access_token', json.access_token);",
                  "  pm.test('Token received', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(json.access_token).to.be.a('string');",
                  "  });",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/x-www-form-urlencoded" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "urlencoded",
              "urlencoded": [
                { "key": "grant_type", "value": "password" },
                { "key": "client_id", "value": "{{client_id}}" },
                { "key": "username", "value": "{{username}}" },
                { "key": "password", "value": "{{password}}" }
              ]
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{keycloak_realm_url}}/protocol/openid-connect/token",
              "host": ["{{keycloak_realm_url}}"],
              "path": ["protocol", "openid-connect", "token"]
            },
            "description": "Obtain an access token using the `password` grant (direct access).\n\nSet `username` and `password` for the user. The tenant's SPA client must have direct access grants enabled.\nThe token is auto-saved to the `access_token` environment variable."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Public",
      "description": "Unauthenticated endpoints — no Bearer token required.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Health Check",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/health",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["health"]
            },
            "description": "Simple health check.\n\nReturns `{ \"status\": \"ok\" }` if the server is running."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Tenant Lookup",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/public/tenant-lookup?email=admin@demo.local",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["public", "tenant-lookup"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "email", "value": "admin@demo.local", "description": "Email to look up" }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Anti-enumeration tenant lookup. Always returns 202; includes `tenantId` only if the email matches a known user."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "CASE Provider v1p0",
      "description": "Standard CASE 1.0 Provider API (read-only).\n\nAuthentication is optional — public-licensed frameworks are accessible without a token.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Discovery (OpenAPI spec)",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/ims/case/v1p0/discovery/imscasev1p0_openapi3_v1p0.json",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["ims", "case", "v1p0", "discovery", "imscasev1p0_openapi3_v1p0.json"]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Get All CFDocuments",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/ims/case/v1p0/CFDocuments?limit=50&offset=0",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["ims", "case", "v1p0", "CFDocuments"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "limit", "value": "50", "description": "Max items (optional)" },
                { "key": "offset", "value": "0", "description": "Pagination offset (optional)" },
                { "key": "sort", "value": "", "disabled": true },
                { "key": "orderBy", "value": "asc", "disabled": true },
                { "key": "filter", "value": "", "disabled": true },
                { "key": "fields", "value": "", "disabled": true },
                { "key": "includeArchived", "value": "false", "disabled": true }
              ]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Get CFDocument",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/ims/case/v1p0/CFDocuments/{{doc_id}}",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["ims", "case", "v1p0", "CFDocuments", "{{doc_id}}"]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Get CFPackage",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "  // Handle both wrapped (v1.1: {CFPackage:{...}}) and flat responses",
                  "  var pkg = json.CFPackage || json;",
                  "",
                  "  function safeId(obj) {",
                  "    if (!obj) return '';",
                  "    return obj.identifier || obj.sourcedId || '';",
                  "  }",
                  "",
                  "  // Document ID",
                  "  var docId = safeId(pkg.CFDocument);",
                  "  if (docId) pm.environment.set('doc_id', docId);",
                  "",
                  "  // First item",
                  "  var items = pkg.CFItems || [];",
                  "  pm.environment.set('item_id', items.length > 0 ? safeId(items[0]) : '');",
                  "",
                  "  // First association",
                  "  var assocs = pkg.CFAssociations || [];",
                  "  pm.environment.set('association_id', assocs.length > 0 ? safeId(assocs[0]) : '');",
                  "",
                  "  // Definitions",
                  "  var defs = pkg.CFDefinitions || {};",
                  "",
                  "  var subjects = defs.CFSubjects || [];",
                  "  pm.environment.set('subject_id', subjects.length > 0 ? safeId(subjects[0]) : '');",
                  "",
                  "  var concepts = defs.CFConcepts || [];",
                  "  pm.environment.set('concept_id', concepts.length > 0 ? safeId(concepts[0]) : '');",
                  "",
                  "  var groupings = defs.CFAssociationGroupings || [];",
                  "  pm.environment.set('association_grouping_id', groupings.length > 0 ? safeId(groupings[0]) : '');",
                  "",
                  "  var itemTypes = defs.CFItemTypes || [];",
                  "  pm.environment.set('item_type_id', itemTypes.length > 0 ? safeId(itemTypes[0]) : '');",
                  "",
                  "  var licenses = defs.CFLicenses || [];",
                  "  pm.environment.set('license_id', licenses.length > 0 ? safeId(licenses[0]) : '');",
                  "",
                  "  // Rubrics",
                  "  var rubrics = pkg.CFRubrics || [];",
                  "  pm.environment.set('rubric_id', rubrics.length > 0 ? safeId(rubrics[0]) : '');",
                  "",
                  "  console.log('Auto-populated IDs from CFPackage:', {",
                  "    doc_id: pm.environment.get('doc_id'),",
                  "    item_id: pm.environment.get('item_id'),",
                  "    association_id: pm.environment.get('association_id'),",
                  "    subject_id: pm.environment.get('subject_id'),",
                  "    concept_id: pm.environment.get('concept_id'),",
                  "    association_grouping_id: pm.environment.get('association_grouping_id'),",
                  "    item_type_id: pm.environment.get('item_type_id'),",
                  "    license_id: pm.environment.get('license_id'),",
                  "    rubric_id: pm.environment.get('rubric_id')",
                  "  });",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/ims/case/v1p0/CFPackages/{{doc_id}}",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["ims", "case", "v1p0", "CFPackages", "{{doc_id}}"]
            },
            "description": "Get a full CFPackage by document ID.\n\n**Auto-populates** all entity ID environment variables (`item_id`, `association_id`, `subject_id`, `concept_id`, `association_grouping_id`, `item_type_id`, `license_id`, `rubric_id`) from the first instance of each entity in the response. Missing entities are set to empty string."
          }
        },
